article.headline: Indiana 94, Savannah St. 65
article.story: BLOOMINGTON, Ind. -- Cody Zeller led four Indiana players in double figures with a career-high 23 points and five rebounds as the Hoosiers defeated Savannah State 94-65 Saturday night at Assembly Hall in the Hoosier Classic. Zeller hit 6 of 7 from the field and 11 of 13 from the foul line for Indiana (4-0). Christian Watford added 19 points, Will Sheehey had 15 and Verdell Jones finished with 11 for the Hoosiers. Preston Blackmon paced the Tigers (1-3) with 11 points. The Hoosiers led by 15 points at the half and extended their lead to as many as 35 late in the game. Indiana shot 57 percent from the field and outscored Savannah State 35-17 at the free throw line.
